Hello, LowEndTalk,&lt;br /&gt;
Pleased to meet you, and thanks for reading our little introduction. We're here to change the way that you think about companies in the LowEnd market.&lt;br /&gt;

What do we actually do that is different from most LowEnd hosts?&lt;br /&gt;

1)	We offer only what we can feasibly provide – No unlimited disk space, no unlimited IP addresses, and no accounts for life. Fair enough. &lt;br /&gt;
2)	We are smart about servers – We believe in good server management practices. Stuffing 300 VPS onto a poor node doesn’t work, and you deserve better than that.&lt;br /&gt;
3)	We care about our clients – Niceness and formalities are great, but when it comes down to the real matters, we bend over backwards for our clients. &lt;br /&gt;


What kind of features separate you HostKana from the rest of the pack? &lt;br /&gt;

1)	Backups – We take weekly backups even of our VPS nodes on a weekly basis, and if you ask us to restore them, we won’t hit you with a fee.&lt;br /&gt;
2)	24/7 Competent Support – We don’t bounce tickets back and forth. We investigate the issue, fix it, and make sure it doesn’t happen again.&lt;br /&gt;
3)	VPS Pools with KVM Virtualization – Almost all companies offering pooled resource VPS solutions are doing so with OpenVZ. By running KVM servers, we are offering you privacy and a higher quality experience. &lt;br /&gt;
4)	DDoS Protection – Given how common DDoS attacks have become, they can happen to anyone, and you need to be protected from them. &lt;br /&gt;

What locations are available?&lt;br /&gt;

1)	Quebec, Canada – OVH&lt;br /&gt;
2)	Roubaix, France – OVH &lt;br /&gt;
3)	Hong Kong, China [Planned]&lt;br /&gt;
4)	Long Angeles, California [Planned] &lt;br /&gt;


**What is actually being offered?**&lt;br /&gt;

VPS Resource Pools&lt;br /&gt;
These are VPS solutions that allow you to create virtual machines on-the-fly. You can make, manage, and delete custom virtual machines. Need a Windows 2008 VM? You’ve got it. What about a 2GB RAM CentOS 6 64-bit machine? Got that too. You can spin them up and delete them immediately, making it very similar to DigitalOcean or Vultr, but with a better price tag, different locations, and other features.  &lt;br /&gt;

